items.question: What is the programme name?
items.answer: The programme is Bachelor of Science (Hons) Intelligent Robotics.

items.question: What is the intake for this programme?
items.answer: The applicable intake is October 2025.

items.question: How long is the Intelligent Robotics programme?
items.answer: The programme duration is three academic years.

items.question: Does the programme include Industrial Training?
items.answer: Yes. Industrial Training is compulsory and carries 6 credit hours.

items.question: What programming skills will students learn?
items.answer: Students learn C/C++, advanced programming, embedded programming, and robotics programming.

items.question: Is Artificial Intelligence covered in this programme?
items.answer: Yes. Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Neural Networks, and Deep Learning are included.

items.question: What robotics-related subjects are offered?
items.answer: Subjects include Robot Programming, Robotics Modelling and Control, Mobile Robots and Drones, and Actuators and Sensors.

items.question: Are embedded systems part of the curriculum?
items.answer: Yes. Students study microcontrollers, embedded systems, and IoT systems.

items.question: What final year projects are required?
items.answer: Students must complete Final Year Project I and Final Year Project II.

items.question: Which AI-related courses are offered by FAIE?
items.answer: Courses include Artificial Intelligence Systems, Machine Learning, Deep Learning and Generative AI, and Data Science Fundamentals.

items.question: Are cybersecurity and software engineering included?
items.answer: Yes. Cybersecurity, Software Engineering, Operating Systems, and Database Systems are part of the syllabus.

items.question: What mathematics subjects are required?
items.answer: Students study Engineering Mathematics, Linear Algebra, Differential Equations, Probability, and Statistics.

items.question: Does the programme include MPU courses?
items.answer: Yes. MPU courses such as Ethics, Sustainability, Integrity, and Leadership are compulsory.

items.question: Is machine vision covered?
items.answer: Yes. Machine Vision and Image Processing is an advanced course in the programme.

items.question: What career skills does this programme prepare students for?
items.answer: The programme prepares students for careers in robotics, AI engineering, embedded systems, automation, and research.

items.question: What is AAP6126 (Industrial Training)?
items.answer: To expose students to the real working environment and get acquainted with the organization structure, business operations and administrative functions. To have hands-on experience in the related fields so that they can relate and reinforce what they have learnt from university. To foster cooperation and to develop synergetic collaboration between industry and university in promoting a knowledgeable society. Pre-Requisite: Completed 60 credit hours

items.question: What topics are covered in AAP6126 (Industrial Training)?
items.answer: Upon passing ALL the 5 assessment components (logbook, company supervisor's assessment, lecturer's visit, presentation, report) separately, the student will accumulate six credit hours. Course Learning

items.question: Are MPU courses compulsory for the Intelligent Robotics bachelor's programme?
items.answer: Yes. MPU (Mata Pelajaran Umum) courses are compulsory for Bachelor's degree students in Malaysia and must be passed before the degree is awarded.

items.question: What are free electives at MMU?
items.answer: Free elective courses at MMU usually have course codes starting with the letter 'F'. They may be taken within or outside a student's area of study, depending on the programme requirements, and their credit hours contribute to the total graduating credit.
